    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-02-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-02-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="993"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d993">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 841.731/318</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Page</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-02-03">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 3, 1915</hi>.</date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 6 p. m.</hi>] </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1582. At my request, the censor counted the whole number of telegrams going both
                    was for three days and reports that the number stopped between the United States
                    and Holland was 14 per cent of the total number and between Scandinavian
                    countries and the United States, 3 per cent.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Ambassador</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
